    - rid: 3818007397566513159
      type: {class: SolvingItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 2
        question:
        - A metal cube has a mass of {m} kg and a volume of {v} cm3. Calculate the
          density of the metal.
        formula: m / v
        variables:
        - variable: m
          name: Mass
          unit: g
          range:
            min: 19.61
            max: 25.97
        - variable: v
          name: Volume
          unit: cm3
          range:
            min: 13
            max: 7.7
        variable: D
        name: Density
        unit: kg/m^3
        rounding: 2
    - rid: 7832858378969808896
      type: {class: MatchingItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 1
        pairs:
        - question:
          - This refers to any substance that characterizes flow.
          - This can either be a liquid or a gas.
          - This has no shape but is denser than a solid.
          correctAnswer: Fluid
        - question:
          - This is defined as the amount of mass per unit volume of a substance.
          - 'It can be computed by simply dividing the mass of the object by its
            volume. '
          correctAnswer: Density
        - question:
          - This is a measure of how much force is applied over a given area.
          - It is the magnitude of the force on a surface per unit area.
          correctAnswer: Pressure
        - question:
          - 'This is the measure of how it resists flowing. '
          - 'This is the measure of how much it opposes flow. '
          correctAnswer: Viscosity
        wrongAnswers:
        - Specific Gravity
        - Poise
        - Liquid
    - rid: 7832858378969808897
      type: {class: FillInTheBlanksItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 1
        question:
        - "\rFill in the blanks with the correct term for each statement. The equation
          for Density (1)__________. The equation for Pressure (2)__________. The
          measurement unit for Viscosity (3)__________.\n"
        correctAnswers:
        - Mass / Volume
        - Force / Area
        - Poise (P)
        wrongAnswers:
        - Power (P)
        - Force * Distance
    - rid: 7832858378969808898
      type: {class: SolvingItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 0
        question:
        - A mechanic tests engine oil. The shear stress is {t} N/m2 and the velocity
          gradientnis {g}. Find the viscosity.
        formula: t / g
        variables:
        - variable: t
          name: Shear Stress
          unit: N/m2
          range:
            min: 4
            max: 8
        - variable: g
          name: Velocity Gradient
          unit: per second
          range:
            min: 1
            max: 9
        variable: V
        name: Viscosity
        unit: Poise
        rounding: 2
    - rid: 7832858379704074288
      type: {class: SolvingItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 1
        question:
        - A gold ring has a mass of {m} g. When measured, it is found to have a volume
          of {v} cm3. Find the density of the gold ring.
        formula: m / v
        variables:
        - variable: m
          name: Mass
