          range:
            min: 12
            max: 18
        - variable: v
          name: Volume
          unit: cm3
          range:
            min: 10
            max: 14
        variable: D
        name: Density
        unit: kg/m^3
        rounding: 2
    - rid: 7832858379704074289
      type: {class: TrueOrFalseItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 0
        question:
        - Determine whether the statement is True or False. Density is defined as
          the amount of volume per unit mass of a substance. It can be computed by
          simply dividing the volume of the object by its mass.
        - Determine whether the statement is True or False. The amount of volume
          per unit mass of a substance is known as its density. It is easily calculated
          by dividing the object's mass by its volume.
        - Determine whether the statement is True or False. A substance's density
          is defined as its volume  per unit mass. It can be computed simply by dividing
          the mass of the object by its volume.
        correctAnswer: 0
    - rid: 7832858379704074290
      type: {class: TrueOrFalseItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 0
        question:
        - Determine whether the statement is True or False. Fluid is any substance
          that characterizes flow, i.e., any substance that has no rigid structure
          is amorphous and conforms to the shape of the receptacle it is in.
        - Determine whether the statement is True or False. Any material that exhibits
          flow is considered fluid; that is, any material that is amorphous, has
          a rigid structure, and takes on the shape of the container it is in.
        - Determine whether the statement is True or False. Any material that flows
          is referred to as fluid; this includes amorphous materials with stiff structures
          that adopt the shape of the container they are in.
        correctAnswer: 1
    - rid: 7832858379704074291
      type: {class: TrueOrFalseItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 0
        question:
        - 'Determine whether the statement is True or False. The amount of force
          exerted over a specific area is measured as pressure. '
        - Determine whether the statement is True or False. It is the amount of force
          per unit area acting on a surface.
        - 'Determine whether the statement is True or False. Pressure is a measurement
          of the force applied across a given area. '
        correctAnswer: 1
    - rid: 7832858379704074292
      type: {class: TrueOrFalseItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 0
        question:
        - Determine whether the statement is True or False. The unit Poise is named
